{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow up on the fundamental building block of Godot’s data types."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Exports","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RunningInEditor"],"anchor":"Articles-and-Tutorials","title":"Articles and Tutorials","generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variants","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Variants","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will often find the type ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" in Godot source code.   Variants are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Godot’s way of passing around certain data types.  They are similar to Swift’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Any"},{"text":" type, but they can only hold Godot types (most structures and classes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that derive from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftGodot.Object"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Creating Variant values","anchor":"Creating-Variant-values","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can create Variants from types that conform to the VariantStorable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"protocol."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This includes the following types:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Godot’s native types: GString, Vector, Rect, Transform, Plane, Quaternion,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"AABB,  Basis, Projection, Int64, NodePaths, RIDs, Callable, GDictionary, Array","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and PackedArrays."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift types that SwiftGodot adds convenience conformances for: Bool, Int, String and Float","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Godot’s objects: e.g. Node, Area2D","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your own subclasses of SwiftGodot.Object type."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Other types that you can manually conform to VariantStorable."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You wrap your data type by calling one of the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"text":" constructors, and then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"you can pass this variant to Godot functions that expect a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, to pass the value "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let trueVaraint = Variant (true)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can get a string representation of a variant by calling "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/description","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["print (trueVariant.description)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you have a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and want to extract its value, you typically use this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pattern:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/\/ This method will return nil if the Variant provided does not contain","\/\/\/ a boolean value.   Otherwise it will contain the boolean stored in the","\/\/\/ variant.","func getBoolValue (variant: Variant) -> Bool? {","    guard let boolValue = Bool (variant) else {","        return nil","    }","    return boolValue","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot provides convenience "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/swift\/blog\/?id=17","isActive":true},{"text":" for all the types","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that can be stored in a Variant.  If the variant does not contain the type you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are requesting the result of the call is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Common Usage Patterns","level":2,"anchor":"Common-Usage-Patterns","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following are some examples of how to work with Variants in practice, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"some idioms suitable to be used with Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the following example, imagine that an API returns a Variant value that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"contains a dictionary with string keys and values are ","type":"text"},{"code":"PackedArrayInt32","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is how you would decode this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/\/ This converts a variant that contains a dictionary of string keys and an ","\/\/\/ array of integers into the native Swift dictionary","func decode (variant: Variant) -> [String: [Int32]]? {","    guard let dict = GDictionary (variant) else {","        \/\/ If the variant is not a dictionary, we return nil","        return nil","    }","    var result = [String: [Int32]] ()","    for (key, value) in dict {","        guard let packedArray = PackedArrayInt32 (value) else {","            \/\/ If the `value` in the dictionary is not of type `PackedArrayInt32`, we ski it","            continue","        }","        result [key] = packedArray","    }","    return result","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The above shows a defensive style of programming, where we prepare for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"possibility that we do not receive a dictionary, or the values in the dictionary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are not of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"PackedArrayInt32","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following examples shows how to encode decode an array that contains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dictionaries with file names and sizes into a Godot ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray"},{"type":"text","text":" with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDictionaries"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func encode(values: [(String,Int)]) -> Variant {","    let array = GArray ()","    for (fileName, size) in values {","        let dict = GDictionary ()","        dict [\"file_name\"] = Variant (fileName)","        dict [\"size\"] = Variant (size)","        array.append (dict)","    }","    return Variant (array)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The next example shows how to decode the result of the above.  The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GDictionary","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" are weakly typed, so the inverse operation takes a defensive","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"approach.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func decode(variant: Variant) -> [(String, Int)]? {","    guard let array = Array (variant) else {","        \/\/ If the variant is not an array, we return nil","        return nil","    }","    var result = [(String, Int)] ()","    for element in array {","        guard let dict = GDictionary (element) else {","            \/\/ If the element in the array is not a dictionary, we skip it","            continue","        }","        guard let fileNameV = dict [\"file_name\"], ","              let fileName = String (filenameV) else {","            \/\/ If the dictionary does not contain a string with the ","            \/\/ key \"file_name\", we skip it","            continue","        }","        guard let sizeV = dict [\"size\"],","              let size = Int (sizeV) else {","            \/\/ If the dictionary does not contain an integer with the key ","            \/\/ \"size\", or if the value can not be converted to an Int,","            \/\/ we skip it","            continue","        }","        result.append ((fileName, size))","    }","    return result","}"]},{"text":"Extracting values from Variants","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Extracting-values-from-Variants"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you know the kind of return that a variant will return, you can invoke the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"failing initializer for that specific type for most structures. Every VariantStorable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will have an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(_ variant: Variant)"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, this is how you could get a Vector2 from a variant:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func distance (variant: Variant) -> Float? {","    guard let vector = Vector2 (variant) else {","\treturn nil","    }","    return vector.length ()","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice that this might return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", which would be the case if the variant"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"contains a different type than the one you were expecting. You can check the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type of the variant by accessing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".gtype"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the variant."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Extracting-Godot-derived-objects-from-Variants","text":"Extracting Godot-derived objects from Variants","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Godot-derived objects are slightly different. If you know you have a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftGodot.Object"},{"text":" stored in the variant, you can call the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/asObject(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instead.  This is a generic method, so you would invoke it like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func getNode (variant: Variant) -> Node? {","    guard let node = variant.asObject (Node.self)) else {","\t  return nil","    }","    return node","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift type inference can also be used, so you can avoid specifying the type if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the compiler can infer the type, like here:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func getNode (variant: Variant) -> Node? {","    var node: Node?","    node = variant.asObject ()","    return node","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reason to rely on calling the "},{"code":"asObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method rather than having a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constructor for the type that takes a variant (like the case for the non-object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types) is that the method can ensure that only one instance of your objects is surfaced to Swift."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Accessing Array Elements","level":2,"anchor":"Accessing-Array-Elements"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the variant types contain arrays, either objects, or a particular"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"packed version of those.   You can access the individual elements of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"those with a convenient subscript provided on the array.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Calling Variant Methods","anchor":"Calling-Variant-Methods"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is possible to invoke the built-in variant methods that exist in the Godot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"universe by using the "},{"code":"call","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method on a Variant.   This is very similar to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call method on an Object."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, you can invoke this generic “size” method on an array to get the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"size of an array, regardless of the specific type of array:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["func printSize (myArray: Variant) {","    switch variant.call(method: \"size\") {","    case .failure(let err):","        print (err)","        return 0","    case .success(let val):","        return Int (val) ?? 0","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variants"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Signals":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","role":"article","title":"Signals","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/signals","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Signals in Godot are used by objects to post interesting events that are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taking place, and can be used by users to easily add behavior and react"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to changes."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/GDictionary":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GDictionary"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GDictionary","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GDictionary","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"GDictionary","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/gdictionary","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A built-in data structure that holds key-value pairs."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","title":"SwiftGodot","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Differences":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","role":"article","title":"SwiftGodot API differences to GDScript","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/differences","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This document lists some common differences between GDSscript and SwiftGodot."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant/asObject(_:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attempts to cast the Variant into a SwiftGodot.Object, if the variant contains a value of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".object"},{"type":"text","text":", then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".object, the value "},{"type":"text","text":"nil` is returned."}],"title":"asObject(_:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/asObject(_:)","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variant\/asobject(_:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"asObject","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"T"},{"text":".Type) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?","kind":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/CustomTypes":{"role":"article","title":"Using Custom Types","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/customtypes","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"You will typically extend the functionality of your Godot game by creating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"classes that derive from one of the various Godot types and adjust the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior accordingly."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Variant objects box various Godot Objects, you create them with one of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"constructors, and you can retrieve the contents using the various extension"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constructors that are declared on the various types that are wrapped.","type":"text"}],"title":"Variant","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Variant"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variant","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RunningInEditor":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RunningInEditor","role":"article","kind":"article","title":"Running Code in the Godot Editor","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/runningineditor","abstract":[{"text":"There are cases where you might want some of your Swift code for your extension","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to run while it is being used in the Godot Editor."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant/description":{"title":"description","type":"topic","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"description","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variant\/description","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/description","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/BindingNodes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes","role":"article","title":"Referencing Nodes from your Scene","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/bindingnodes","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"You will find yourself referencing nodes from a scene in your code.   In"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GDScript, that is usually achieved by using the dollar sign and the name of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object you want to reference."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/GArray":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A built-in data structure that holds a sequence of elements."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GArray","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"GArray","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/garray","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GArray"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/swift/blog/?id=17":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"failable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initializers","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/swift\/blog\/?id=17","title":"failable initializers","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/swift\/blog\/?id=17"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Exports":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Exports","role":"article","title":"Exports","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/exports","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In Godot, class members can be exported. This means their value gets saved along"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the resource (such as the scene) they’re attached to. They will also be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"available for editing in the property editor. Exporting is done by using the"}]}}}